{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"divinable-herbal-panda","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Description\nProve portability end-to-end: run the code_health lens against a Python client fixture AND a non-Python client fixture (Go or TypeScript), asserting real values with analyzers present and honest Unavailable when the [metrics] extra / tools are absent. This is the epic headline acceptance criterion.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Fixture repos: one Python, one non-Python (Go or TS), each with a rebar ticket store shape sufficient for the run.\n- [ ] With analyzers present: code_health metrics compute for BOTH languages.\n- [ ] With extra/tools absent: code_health reports Unavailable (no crash, no fabricated data) for both.\n- [ ] agent_process + git-delta metrics compute for both (already language-agnostic).\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Interface/E2E test covering both fixtures and both present/absent states.\n\n## Dependencies: Child 7 (and 4,5,6)\n## Files likely touched: tests/interfaces/test_metrics_polyglot.py (new), tests/fixtures/* (new)\n## Estimated scope: M","id":"a532-4e67-562c-4893","parent_id":"839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051","priority":2,"tags":["metrics","code-health"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Cross-language validation: code_health on a Python and a non-Python client project"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784517475532064001,"uuid":"dc718833-bd10-4a8a-8f54-11a144c29dca"}